configSetPrices.disclaimer:
Calculator

The information presented on this website is based on data available at the time. Design, specifications, price, and production dates are subject to change without notice and pertain specifically to United Kingdom vehicles. Some features and options may be unavailable when your vehicle enters production.

Base price includes VAT and a United Kingdom plug-in vehicle grant of £5,000. Price may not include some local and regionally required fees. VAT rates are subject to change.

Hire Purchase

The monthly hire purchase payments have been calculated by Tesla Motors Limited from data provided by BMW Financial Services (GB) Limited trading as Alphera Financial Services. The quotes are on a monthly basis calculated using a 72 month term (as indicated) and the 30% down payment and interest rate of 5.9% APR as indicated.

The estimated fuel savings are based on the assumptions specified on an annual basis. Please refer to Alphera Financial Services for full details of hire purchase terms and conditions.

Wheels

There are different advantages to the 21-inch and 19-inch wheels. For example, the 21-inch wheels generally provide increased handling whereas the 19-inch wheels wear less quickly and provide more protection from obstacles and poor road conditions.
configSetPrices.resale_value_guarantee_text: Tesla guarantees the resale value of your Model S to be similar to or greater than other cars in its class. After three years, you can trade in your Model S for 50% of the original base price plus 43% of options. Learn more about the Tesla Resale Value Guarantee.
configSetPrices.incentives_txt: Electric vehicle incentives include a £5,000 plug-in vehicle grant and waivers for road tax, company car tax and London congestion charges. Learn more about incentives.

PA01.name: No Paint Armor
PA01.description:

  • Front and rear rocker panels
  • Rear bumper fascia

Depending on the angle of sunlight, seams between protected and unprotected paint areas will be visible, particularly on white and pearl white cars.

configSetPrices.gas_disclaimer:
Electric Vehicle Incentives

Electric vehicle incentives include a £5,000 plug-in vehicle grant and waivers for road tax, company car tax and London congestion charges. Click here for more information.

Additional incentives can be calculated from Benefit in Kind savings from driving a Model S as a company employee. If you are an employee driving Model S under a company car scheme and in the 40% tax bracket, you will pay just 5% Benefit in Kind taxes compared to the 29% Benefit in Kind taxes required of an employee driving an internal combustion vehicle of 174 g/km.

Petrol Savings

Electric vehicles are less expensive to fuel than petrol powered vehicles. The average person drives approximately 12,000 miles and spends around £1,600 on petrol per year. In comparison, the cost of electricity to power Model S over the same distance is ten times lower. Over the five year average length of car ownership, that's approximately £6,000 in petrol savings.

We've assumed a fuel economy of 39.2 miles per gallon for a comparable petrol powered car. We've also assumed the national average of £0.14 per kilowatt hour for electricity, 10% charging on Tesla's Supercharger network enabling free long distance travel, and £1.17 per liter for premium petrol over the next five years.

Tesla Model S drivers are in band A for CO2 omissions and pay no standard road tax compared with, by way of example, standard road tax of £290 in the first year and £205 annually subsequently for a petrol or diesel band H car.
